QueryText: Q13 What are the management practices against collar rot of apple
KccAns: Q13 What are the management practices against collar rot of appleAns: Avoid water logging in the orchard Do not let water pool at crown region Keep the graft union 20-25cm above ground level Use clonal root stocks as M-2 M-4 M-9 M-26 M-113 M-114 For curing the ailing tree irrigate 30cm radius around tree trunk with copper oxychloride1000-2000 gm200L water or Mancozeb or Ridomil MZ or Metalaxyl or Unilax 600 gm200L water During winters: Remove the soil around the collar region and expose the affected portion to sun Remove the affected bark and apply chaubatia paste or copper oxychloride paste  300gm10L water

QueryText: regarding collar rot in apple trees
KccAns: IMPROVE THE DRAINAGE OF YOUR ORCHARD AND  APPLY BORDEAUX PASTE OR CHAUBATIA PASTE  ON THE AFFECTED AREA AFTER CLEANING THE AREA WITH SHARP KNIFE Bordeaux Paste consists of same constituents as that of Bordeaux mixture but it is in the form of a paste as the quantity of water used is too little It is nothing but 10 per cent Bordeaux mixture and is prepared by mixing 1 kg of copper sulphate and 1 kg of lime in 10 litres of water The method of mixing solution is similar to that of Bordeaux mixture It is a wound dresser and used to protect the wounded portions cut ends of trees etc against the infection by fungal pathogens
